.SH NAME
snd_soc_component_init_regmap \- Initialize regmap instance for the component
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_soc_component_init_regmap
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "struct regmap *regmap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
The component for which to initialize the regmap instance
.IP "regmap" 12
The regmap instance that should be used by the component
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allows deferred assignment of the regmap instance that is
associated with the component. Only use this if the regmap instance is not
yet ready when the component is registered. The function must also be called
before the first IO attempt of the component.
